@everyone - Great news from the Tiny Tapeout team and @tnt, it seems that the Tiny Tapeout chips on Run #1 are working! You can see a bunch of the results on the Tiny Tapeout Discord (https://discord.gg/QRZSJ4Nz) in the https://discord.com/channels/1009193568256135208/1492403296747651072 channel.

We still have a few issues to fix around the chip-on-board bonding and will continue to working on that before doing the final runs. @Leo Moser (mole99) has also discovered some interesting artifacts through microscope imagery.

I believe most other groups with 1x1 projects should have also received their die and I'm excited to see how testing goes. Please do report on the discord and share what you are doing and any issues you are having. Others might be have similar problems and be able to help you diagnose problems and offer possible fixes.

@everyone - Just a quick reminder that there is just under 24 hours left to get the early bird discount! 

You have till 30 April 2026 @ 11:59 PM AoE (see in your timezone @ https://www.timeanddate.com/worldclock/fixedtime.html?iso=20260430T2359&p1=3399 ) before the prices for slots go up.

PS I'll also be attending Hackaday Supercon Europe in Italy and will have a bunch of silicon in hand to show off.
